 mutating / destructive, with eval/raw/run treated as arbitrary mutation and local exports requiring explicit no-overwrite paths. Pairs with sk-interface-design (design judgment) and sk-code (adapting exports into an app). Modeled on mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-open-design.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/hf-model-server.cjs:\n  Line 49: const LOOPBACK_BIND_HOSTS = Object.freeze(['127.0.0.1', '::1', 'localhost']);\n\n  Line 95:   if (raw.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 100:     return `tcp://${url.hostname}:${url.port || (url.protocol === 'https:' ? '443' : '80')}`;\n\n  Line 114:   if (env.SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR?.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 125:   if (!socketPath.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 138:     return `tcp://${address.address}:${address.port}`;\n\n  Line 151: // A tcp:// target takes its host verbatim from the operator URL. Binding a\n\n  Line 156:   if (typeof target !== 'string' || !target.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 173:     'model inference to the network. Use a loopback host (127.0.0.1/::1/localhost), or set ' +\n\n  Line 277:     if (target.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 288:       server.listen(Number.parseInt(url.port, 10), url.hostname || '127.0.0.1');\n\n  Line 299:   if (!target.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 306:     if (error.code !== 'EADDRINUSE' || target.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 332:   if (!target.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n  Line 911:     const url = new URL(request.url || '/', 'http://127.0.0.1');\n\n  Line 977:     if (state.listenTarget && !state.listenTarget.startsWith('tcp://')) {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs:\n  Line 630:     (storedSocketPath.startsWith('tcp://') || fs.existsSync(storedSocketPath))\n\n  Line 639:   if (!socketPath.startsWith('tcp://') && !fs.existsSync(socketPath)) {\n\n  Line 944:   const pidDir = socketPath.startsWith('tcp://') ? resolvedDbDir() 